A RESOLUTION
1 Designating the month of March as Autoimmune Disease Awareness Month; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, autoimmune diseases impact thousands of Georgians each year,
4 disproportionately affecting women and people of color, but awareness and understanding
5 of these diseases remains low; and
6 WHEREAS, recognizing autoimmune diseases during the month of March will help raise
7 public awareness, encourage early detection and diagnosis, and support research and policy
8 initiatives aimed at improving patient outcomes; and
9 WHEREAS, designating the month of March as Autoimmune Disease Awareness Month
10 will demonstrate the State of Georgia's commitment to health equity and highlight its
11 dedication to supporting Georgians facing these chronic, often invisible, illnesses.
12 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
13 the members of this body:
14 (1) Designate March of each year as Autoimmune Disease Awareness Month in the State
15 of Georgia;
