16 (2) Encourage officials and departments of state, county, and municipal governments,
17 businesses, and all citizens to participate in appropriate programs and activities that
18 facilitate increased awareness and education about autoimmune diseases throughout each
19 March to commemorate Autoimmune Disease Awareness Month; and
20 (3) Respectfully request the Governor to issue annually a proclamation recognizing
21 March in the State of Georgia as Autoimmune Awareness Month and call upon the
22 people in the State of Georgia to observe the month with appropriate programs and
23 activities.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
25 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to
26 Governor Brian Kemp and the public and the press.
